# 7. リベンジ紅葉狩り

Shizuku: We've climbed quite far now.
Tsukasa: Yes. Based on this map, the best spot for viewing leaves should be just up ahead...
Saki: Hey, look! There's the observation deck!
Saki: It's reattempt time! We've gotta take as many pictures as we can!
Shizuku: Yes, let's try getting closer!
Shiho: There's no need to rush. It's not like the leaves are going anywhere.
Tsukasa: Hm? I thought I felt a raindrop just now...
Saki: Huh?
Shizuku: I felt one as well. Is a raincloud passing over us?
Saki: Wait, but the forecast said it wouldn't rain!
Tsukasa: Nothing for it. We need to hurry and see the leaves before it really starts coming down...!
Shiho: Uh oh...
Saki: Wow, here it comes!
Tsukasa: What terrible timing... Did you all bring umbrellas?
Shizuku: Yes, we both brought compact umbrellas.
Tsukasa: That includes you, Saki. You'll catch a cold if you don't stay dry.
Saki: *Sob* But we were so close... It was sunny, and the leaves were right there...
Saki: We failed our mission...
Shiho: ...
Shiho: (Right. Up here in the mountains, the weather can change in an instant...)
Shiho: (The goal of this trip was to go leaf-viewing, so we probably should've done this first.)
Shiho: (Then we would've been able to see the leaves like we wanted...)
Shiho: (It's my fault for not scheduling this activity first.)
Shizuku: It may be raining now...
Shizuku: But this is also really nice.
Shiho: Huh...?
Shizuku: I don't know if it's because the rain made them wet, but these leaves seem much more vibrant compared to when the sun was out just now.
Shizuku: I remember feeling so sad when it rained like this when we were children, but I think I'm really enjoying leaf-viewing in this weather.
Tsukasa: Yes, I'm inclined to agree with Shizuku here.
Tsukasa: Just as the leaves appear one way when it's sunny, they'll look completely different when it's rainy...
Saki: Yeah, but...
Saki: *Gasp* Tsukasa, there's a leaf stuck to your umbrella...
Tsukasa: Oh, it looks like it's a part of my umbrella's design now! This wouldn't have happened if it were still sunny.
Saki: Yeah, it's really pretty...!
Shizuku: Hehe. We must be very blessed, getting to experience so much.
Shiho: Yeah...
Shiho: (I really am nothing like these three.)
Shiho: (I'm always worrying about not wasting time and stuff.)
Shiho: (Even for this trip, I obsessed over coming up with the most efficient itinerary...)
Shiho: (And I immediately thought it fell apart the second something unexpected happened.)
Shiho: (But they don't care about any of that. Instead, they're...)
Tsukasa: The answer to that is simple! A physical ticket adds to the sentimental value of this trip!
Saki: Because I know I'm gonna pick the most delicious grapes in this vineyard!
Shizuku: Doesn't this look like a piece of art?
Shiho: (They're able to fully enjoy what's right in front of them...)
Shiho: (They cherish every second of every moment.)
Shiho: (Sure, that leads to us taking a lot of detours and having to clean up extra messes...)
Shiho: (But when I'm with them, I'm able to see the benefits of all the things that I refused to consider...)
Shiho: (At least, that's what I feel.)
Shiho: I'm glad we came here today.
Shiho: Especially since we got to see such a beautiful view.
Shizuku: Shii...!
Saki: Hehe. Thank goodness! I'm so glad to hear that you're having fun, Shiho!
Tsukasa: Yes, I'm also glad. I was honestly a little worried, since you almost literally carried this entire trip on your back.
Shiho: I sure did, and don't you forget it.
Tsukasa: Oof...
Shiho: I'm only teasing.
Saki: Oh...!
Saki: Look, it's starting to clear up a little!
Tsukasa: Oh, you're right! Sunbeams are beginning to poke through the clouds...
Shizuku & Saki: Oh...! Wow...!
Saki: The leaves... They're sparkling so much...!
Shiho: It's beautiful...
Shizuku: Yes, very...
Tsukasa: The contrast between these leaves and the sunset... What a stunning view!
Shizuku: Hehe. On top of seeing the leaves when it rained, we got to see them as the sky cleared back up.
Tsukasa: This is all thanks to the plan you made for us, Shiho...
Tsukasa: Yes, we can't thank you enough! This place has been an absolute feast for our eyes!
Saki: Yeah! Thanks for putting so much thought into this!
Shiho: Wait, this is all just a big coincidence. To be frank, things didn't actually go according to plan.
Shiho: (Still...)
Shiho: (I am glad to see them all smiling like this...)
